encodings.2: Core facilities management software incl. compliance & risk management (e.g., inspections, health & safety checks, certifications), Development & construction (e.g., tracking when building is undergoing development or refurbishment), Energy compliance
encodings.3: Asset management software (reporting across multiple sites and entire property portfolio)
encodings.4: Investment management software (e.g., fund admin, performance reporting)
encodings.7: Other payment related services (e.g., digital arrears management, Integrated loan access, Integrated insurance)
encodings.8: Building Relationship Management (BRM) (e.g., building inventory, energy consumption rate, occupancy rate, ESG analytics, sustainability reporting)
encodings.9: Customer Relationship Management (CRM) (e.g., Lead management, listing syndication, tenant portal, self-service, helpdesk, communications)
encodings.10: Workforce Relationship Management (WRM) (e.g., employee scheduling, planning)
encodings.11: Supplier Relationship Management (SRM) (e.g., vendor & partners, craftsperson management)

Which of the following providers you would consider your main provider for property management software?

english_uk translation for: Auto-other QA_MAIN_971_OTH
Generally, how frequently does your company re-evaluate property management software providers?
How easy or difficult would it be for your company to switch property management software provider in the next 3 years?
What would encourage you to switch your current property management software provider?

encodings.1: Better ability to ensure regulatory compliance
encodings.3: Ability to purchase additional software modules
encodings.4: Better suited for management of higher number of residential units or management across multiple geographies
encodings.7: Better level of integration ability with another vendor
encodings.8: Better customer support with another vendor
encodings.10: Better ability to customize and tailor solution to needs of my company
encodings.11: Better reputation, recommended by friend/ colleague, positive prior experience

column_description: Other
english_uk translation for: Auto-other QA_SWITCHING_WHY_97_OTH
And what would be the main barriers to switching from your current property management software provider?

encodings.6: Difficulty of training workforce on new vendor
encodings.10: Dependence on specific features unique to the current vendor
encodings.11: Business continuity concerns during transition (e.g., disruption to operations)
encodings.12: Corporate policy (i.e., mandated use of specific set of Vendor(s))

column_description: Other
english_uk translation for: Auto-other QA_SWITCHING_BARRIERS_97_OTH
How likely or unlikely are you to bring all your software under one provider in the next 3 years?
Why would you consider consolidating all your software under one provider?

encodings.1: More cost effective to use a singular platform
encodings.2: Easier to manage network security through a single platform
encodings.3: Easier to integrate one platform vs. solutions from different vendors
encodings.4: Greater ability to scale based on organization needs
encodings.5: More consistent performance of networking solutions through using one platform
encodings.6: Easier to adopt other / adjacent solutions with same platform provider
encodings.7: Limited budget to switch to best-of-breed vendor(s)
encodings.8: Less risk by using only one platform

column_description: Other
english_uk translation for: Auto-other QA_CONSOLIDATE_WHY_97_OTH
Why would you not consider consolidating all your software under one provider?

encodings.1: More cost effective to use a multiple platforms
encodings.2: Easier to manage network security through multiple platforms
encodings.3: Harder to integrate one platform vs. solutions from different vendors
encodings.4: Greater ability to scale based on organization needs
encodings.5: More consistent performance of networking solutions through using multiple platforms
encodings.6: Easier to adopt other / adjacent solutions when using multiple providers
encodings.7: Limited budget to consolidate to one vendor(s)
encodings.8: Less risk by using multiple platforms

column_description: Other
english_uk translation for: Auto-other QA_CONSOLIDATE_WHY_NOT_97_OTH
Which provider would you integrate all your software under?
Other
english_uk translation for: Auto-other QA_ONEPROVIDER_971_OTH
What functionality are you using?

encodings.2: Payment reconciliation (e.g., account reconciliation for rent and deposit payments)
